title: For Sale:  Ithaca NID 4E 20 Gauge - 32" VENT RIB, ALL OPTIONS, FACTORY 99%
postcontent:
According to Walt Snyder's book, "The Ithaca Gun Company; From the Beginning" there were only 45,000 Ithaca NID (New Ithaca Doubles) produced from 1926 to 1946. But when analyzing the production of Grade 4 and above guns, there were only 560 Grade 4 guns produced in all gauges, with about 150 or less in 20ga. guns. This gun, sn455798 built in 1929, is a FULLY OPTIONED TRAP CONFIGURED GUN, AND IS ONE OF A TINY HANDFUL OF GUNS SO PRODUCED. In near mint condition, with ULTRA RARE 32" vent rib barrels, beavertail forend, SST, ejectors, double ivory beads, factory pad, this is a true investment quality shotgun with CONDITION, RARITY, AND DESIRABLE AND RARE OPTIONS. And of course, it has that fully figured Ithaca walnut with the fancy flor-de-lis checkering that sets the Ithaca guns apart from all others. This is a great gun!

The gun weighs 7 1/4lbs. and balances nicely between the hands. This is not a lightweight field gun you would want to walk all day with, but a fantastic gun for ducks or doves, high volume pigeon or crows, and maybe the perfect sporting clays or trap gun. The weight will greatly reduce felt recoil and the long weight forward barrels will keep your swing smooth and moving; the perfect scenario for the above mentioned uses.

title: For Sale:  Abbiatico & Salvinelli 12 Gauge Over & Under
postcontent: What a fantastic work of art this gun is! Built in 2006 when some of their finest shotguns were produced, before the expansion in the late 2000's as FAMARS. Most truly knowledgeable fine shotgun experts acknowledge Abbiatico & Salvinelli (A & S) guns from this period as some of the finest shotguns ever made, with meticulous polishing and fitting internally, awesome wood and 28 lpi checkering, and of course that engraving! A & S is often credited with establishing the Italian engravers and the art of bulino style engraving as the pinnacle of the engraver's world. This gun was engraved by Rinniui, an acknowledged master engraver who regularly worked on $100,000 guns, in a very attractive deep relief Celtic style reminiscent of guns of Scottish decent. There is no wear on this gun, with 99% blue and factory finish overall, perfect checkering and only a few handling marks on the EXHIBITION WOOD. Weighing 7 3/4lbs. and balanced 1/4" in front of the hinge pin, single selective trigger, drop out trigger group, Boss style action, perfect mechanicals, perfect screws, screw in chokes, and nearly new in all ways, this gun is a bargain at less than 1/2 the price of new

title: For Sale:  Ithaca NID 4E 20 Gauge - 32" VENT RIB, ALL OPTIONS, FACTORY 99%
postcontent:
According to Walt Snyder's book, "The Ithaca Gun Company; From the Beginning" there were only 45,000 Ithaca NID (New Ithaca Doubles) produced from 1926 to 1946. But when analyzing the production of Grade 4 and above guns, there were only 560 Grade 4 guns produced in all gauges, with about 150 or less in 20ga. guns. This gun, sn455798 built in 1929, is a FULLY OPTIONED TRAP CONFIGURED GUN, AND IS ONE OF A TINY HANDFUL OF GUNS SO PRODUCED. In near mint condition, with ULTRA RARE 32" vent rib barrels, beavertail forend, SST, ejectors, double ivory beads, factory pad, this is a true investment quality shotgun with CONDITION, RARITY, AND DESIRABLE AND RARE OPTIONS. And of course, it has that fully figured Ithaca walnut with the fancy flor-de-lis checkering that sets the Ithaca guns apart from all others. This is a great gun!

The gun weighs 7 1/4lbs. and balances nicely between the hands. This is not a lightweight field gun you would want to walk all day with, but a fantastic gun for ducks or doves, high volume pigeon or crows, and maybe the perfect sporting clays or trap gun. The weight will greatly reduce felt recoil and the long weight forward barrels will keep your swing smooth and moving; the perfect scenario for the above mentioned uses.
